Fstatus%2F1678474611942367249%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecountless%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FKhoaVuUmn%2Fstatus%2F1539078764239458304%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparodies%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20a%20nugget%20of%20truth%20in%20the%20silly%20message.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESingle-family%20zoning%20dominates%20even%20the%20densest%20US%20cities.%20Townhomes%2C%20apartment%20buildings%2C%20and%20even%20duplexes%20are%20illegal%20to%20build%20in%20vast%20swaths%20of%20urban%20residential%20neighborhoods%20that%20are%20instead%20reserved%20for%20lower-density%20detached%20houses.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2019%2F06%2F18%2Fupshot%2Fcities-across-america-question-single-family-zoning.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAbout%2075%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20residentially-zoned%20land%20prohibits%20anything%20but%20single-family%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHomes%20are%20often%20not%20allowed%20near%20shops%2C%20restaurants%2C%20and%20grocery%20stores.%20Restrictive%20land%20use%20laws%20have%20helped%20create%20a%20US%20housing%20shortage%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F03%2F08%2Fhomes%2Fhousing-shortage%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esomewhere%20around%20six%20million%20units%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20as%20home%20prices%20and%20rents%20become%20increasingly%20unaffordable%2C%20the%20American%20public%20is%20starting%20to%20take%20issue%20with%20policies%20that%20restrict%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELarge%20majorities%20say%20they%20support%20policies%20that%20would%20facilitate%20more%20%E2%80%94%20and%20denser%20%E2%80%94%20housing%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewtrusts.org%2Fen%2Fresearch-and-analysis%2Farticles%2F2023%2F11%2F30%2Fsurvey-finds-large-majorities-favor-policies-to-enable-more-housing%3Futm_campaign%3Dcommunities_hpi________%26utm_source%3Dtwitter_trusts%26utm_medium%3Dsocial%26utm_content%3D_____photo_%26utm_term%3D___%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20Pew%20Research%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20in%20September%20and%20published%20last%20week.%20The%20survey%20asked%20respondents%20about%2010%20different%20pro-housing%20policies.%20The%20most%20popular%20included%20streamlining%20the%20permitting%20process%3B%20legalizing%20apartments%20in%20commercial%20areas%20and%20near%20transit%3B%20allowing%20basements%2C%20garages%2C%20and%20attics%20to%20be%20turned%20into%20accessory%20dwelling%20units%3B%20and%20allowing%20student%20housing%20and%20affordable%20homes%20on%20property%20owned%20by%20non-profits%2C%20including%20churches.%20The%20least%20popular%20policy%20%E2%80%94%20which%20got%2049%25%20support%20%E2%80%94%20involved%20allowing%20smaller%20home%20lot%20sizes.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20American%20cities%20and%20states%20make%20the%20building%20approval%20process%20excruciatingly%20slow%2C%20and%20don't%20allow%20the%20kind%20of%20density%20these%20policies%20would%20promote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20support%20for%20pro-housing%20policies%20also%20crossed%20partisan%20and%20demographic%20lines.%20Majorities%20of%20Republicans%2C%20Democrats%2C%20and%20independents%20supported%20the%20eight%20most%20popular%20policies.%20And%20majorities%20of%20both%20renters%20and%20homeowners%20supported%20nine%20of%20the%2010%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20data%20aligns%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyimbys-winning-lower-house-prices-rents-build-more-homes-neighborhoods-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20growing%20popularity%20of%20YIMBYism%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20pro-building%20%26quot%3Byes%20in%20my%20backyard%26quot%3B%20philosophy%2C%20which%20advocates%20abundant%20housing%20to%20bring%20down%20costs.%20States%20across%20the%20country%2C%20including%20California%2C%20Washington%2C%20Montana%2C%20and%20Maine%2C%20have%20passed%20housing%20policies%20similar%20t