%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEmbracing%C2%A0%26quot%3Bradical%20flexibility%26quot%3B%20can%20help%20employers%20attract%20and%20retain%20workers%2C%20an%20expert%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20looks%20like%20the%20holy%20grail%20for%20any%20job%3A%20four%20days'%20work%20for%20five%20days'%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F4-day-workweek-companies-workers-implementing-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efour-day%20workweek%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20latest%20buzzy%20example%20of%20how%20some%20employers%20hope%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-life-balance-job-satisfaction-burnout-great-resignation-office-return-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecombat%20worker%20burnout%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Other%20methods%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-instagram-post-rto-wfh-work-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epretty%20offices%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaid-sabbaticals-leave-company-productivity-employee-retention-wellbeing-loyalty-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epaid%20sabbaticals%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20legacies%20of%20the%20pandemic%3A%20remote%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20what's%20needed%20most%2C%20workplace%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20is%20greater%20flexibility%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20more%20thoughtful%20definition%20of%20what%20that%20means%20for%20each%20company%20or%20industry.%20Employers%20and%20their%20workers%20have%20to%20let%20go%20of%20the%20tendency%20to%20fear%20change%2C%20and%20instead%2C%20radically%20rethink%20how%20we%20work%2C%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlexibility%20might%20apply%20to%20where%20people%20work%2C%20when%20they%20do%20it%2C%20what%20processes%20or%20tools%20they%20use%2C%20and%20even%20whom%20they%20work%20with%2C%20experts%20said.%20Essentially%2C%20it's%20about%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20about%20giving%20people%20more%20control%20over%20their%20workweeks%20so%20that%20they%20can%20balance%20the%20things%20that%20are%20important%20at%20work%20and%20personally%2C%26quot%3B%20Ryan%20Anderson%2C%20the%20VP%20of%20global%20research%20and%20insights%20at%20MillerKnoll%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELetting%20workers%20pick%20their%20schedules%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOffering%20flexibility%20in%20the%20workplace%20isn't%20a%20one-size-fits-all%20solution.%20Nurses%2C%20for%20example%2C%20generally%20aren't%20asking%20to%20work%20from%20home%2C%20Will%20Howard%2C%20director%20of%20HR%20research%20%26amp%3B%20advisory%20services%20at%20McLean%2C%20a%20research%20firm%2C%20told%20BI.%20Yet%20it's%20common%20in%20nursing%20to%20trade%20shifts%2C%20he%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20variations%20involve%20setting%20%26quot%3Bcore%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20when%20everyone%20must%20be%20working%2C%20Howard%20said%2C%20but%20then%20allowing%20workers%20to%20choose%20the%20other%20hours%20that%20are%20convenient%20for%20them.%20In%20other%20cases%2C%20it%20might%20involve%20letting%20workers%20pick%20their%20own%20schedules%20or%20offering%20summer%20hours%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnconventional%20setups%20can%20be%20conventional%20in%20some%20jobs%2C%20Howard%20said.%20The%20work%20patterns%20of%20pilots%20or%20those%20who%20toil%20away%20on%20oil%20rigs%20can%20vary%20widely.%20Bosses%20who%20look%20for%20unique%20work%20setups%20can%20find%20examples%20that%20could%20serve%20as%20models%2C%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20people%20who%20have%20been%20doing%20six%20months%20on%20six%20months%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20Howard%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20types%20of%20flexibility%20exist%20elsewhere.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdding%20elasticity%20into%20work%20often%20comes%20down%20to%20the%20person%20or%20the%20organization.%20%26quot%3BThe%20hardest%20part%20for%20leaders%20or%20managers%20to%20embrace%20is%20that%20it's%20going%20to%20look%20different%20for%20everyone%20to%20some%20degree%2C%20because%20everyone's%20definition%20of%20balance%20is%20going%20to%20look%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20Kristen%20Lipton%2C%20a%20managing%20director%20at%20Gallup%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20balance%20might%20be%20difficult%20to%20achieve%2C%20in%20part%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaders-dont-trust-remote-employees-are-productive-microsoft-study-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebosses%20don't%20always%20trust%20their%20workers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20not%20all%20workers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foveremployed-workers-secret-two-multiple-jobs-salaries-tech-tips-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehave%20faith%20in%20their%20employers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20limits%20to%20what%20can%20ultimately%20be%20offered%2C%20according%20to%20Steven%20Rogelberg%2C%20an%20organizational%20psychologist%20and%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%20at%20Charlotte.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20be%20flexible%2C%20but%20we%20need%20to%20be%20reasonable.%20And%20both%20parties%20need%20to%20be%20reasonable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERogelberg%20said%20it's%20not%20outlandish%20for%20an%20employer%20to%20require%20people%20to%20show%20up%20to%20an%20office%20two%20or%20three%20days%20a%20week.%20%26quot%3BSomeone's%20paying%20you%20to%20do%20a%20job.%20Like%20you're%20not%20entitled%20to%20say%2C%20'Yeah%2C%20I%20want%20everything.%20I%20can%20work%20any%20way%20I%20want%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20not%20realistic.%20There's%20a%20coming%20together%20that%20needs%20to%20happen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHelping%20managers%20%26quot%3Bunstick%26quot%3B%20how%20work%20gets%20done%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EManagers%20play%20a%20key%20role%20in%20helping%20foster%20flexibility%20by%20asking%20workers%20what%20flexibility%20means%20to%20them%2C%20Lipton%20said.%20Because%20workers%20have%20different%20talents%20and%20varying%20needs%2C%20a%20different%20approach%20might%20be%20needed%20depending%20on%20the%20person%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnderstanding%20the%20role%20of%20the%20manager%20is%20so%20difficult%2C%20because%20you're%20trying%20to%20balance%20the%20expectations%20that%20are%20coming%20down%20from%20the%20organization%20about%20some%20of%20these%20policies%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20effective%20ways%20for%20injecting%20flexibility%20into%20a%20workplace%20is%20by%20establishing%20change%20at%20a%20team%20level%2C%20Anderson%20said.%20Employers%20might%20uncover%20new%20ways%20to%20combat%20burnout%20by%20giving%20team%20leaders%20the%20power%20to%20%26quot%3Bunstick%26quot%3B%20themselves%20from%20the%20way%20work%20has%20long%20been%20done%20at%20an%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERadical%20flexibility%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20no%20surprise%20that%20increased%20say%20over%20their%20workdays%20is%20something%20employees%20want%3A%20More%20than%2080%25%20want%20some%20autonomy%20on%20where%20they%20work%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffutureforum.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2FFuture-Forum-Pulse-Report-Winter-2022-2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EFuture%20Forum%20study%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20in%20early%202023.%20But%20what%20more%20workers%20%E2%80%94%2093%25%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20seek%20is%20schedule%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20going%20beyond%20some%20form%20of%20remote%20work.%20For%20employers%20that%20are%20struggling%20to%20keep%20workers%20happy%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0or%20to%20attract%20them%20at%20all%20%E2%80%94%20being%20flexible%20means%20rethinking%20how%20roles%20are%20set%20up%2C%20Emily%20Rose%20McRae%2C%20senior%20director%20analyst%20at%20the%20research%20firm%20Gartner%2C%20told%20BI.%20A%20shortage%20of%20workers%20in%20many%20industries%20means%20employers%20offer%20what%20she%20calls%20%26quot%3Bradical%20flexibility.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20if%2C%20instead%2C%20employees%20gave%20you%20what%20their%20availability%20was%3F%26quot%3B%20McRae%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20bosses%20might%20work%20with%20employees%20to%20agree%20on%20a%20minimum%20number%20of%20hours%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20willing%20to%20do%20things%20differently%20is%20often%20good%20for%20business%2C%20McRae%20said.%20Gartner%20research%20found%20that%20when%20employers%20go%20big%20on%20flexibility%20%E2%80%94%20and%20don't%20limit%20it%20to%20when%20and%20where%20people%20work%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20share%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gartner.com%2Fen%2Farticles%2Fthe-secret-to-productive-employees-a-radical-shift-in-work-flexibility%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployees%20who%20are%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20performers%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20jumps%20by%2040%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20approaches%20can%20also%20help%20pull%20in%20workers.%20That's%20something%20that's%20been%20difficult%20for%20many%20employers%20since%20the%20economy%20began%20its%20rebound%20from%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20that%20say%20they%20can't%20offer%20remote%20work%20or%20other%20forms%20of%20flexibility%20are%20often%20the%20ones%20struggling%20to%20draw%20workers%2C%20McRae%20said.%20She%20said%20employers%20that%20are%20willing%20to%20reconsider%20how%20work%20gets%20done%20at%20their%20organization%20can%20%26quot%3Bmassively%20increase%26quot%3B%20their%20talent%20pool%2C%20hang%20onto%20workers%20longer%2C%20and%20get%20better%20results%20from%20their%20teams%20because%20people's%20lives%20are%20better%20balanced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnderson%20also%20sees%20giving%20workers%20more%20options%20as%20a%20wise%20move%20for%20employers%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20smart%20approach%20is%20to%20support%20choice%2C%20and%20then%20provide%20great%20choices%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20something%20to%20share%20about%20what%20you're%20seeing%20in%20your%20workplace%3F%20Insider%20would%20like%20to%20hear%20from%20you.%20Email%20our%20workplace%20team%20from%20a%20nonwork%20device%20at%20%3Cu%3Ethegrind%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%20with%20your%20story%20or%20to%20ask%20for%20one%20of%20our%20reporter's%20Signal%20numbers.%20Or%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Echeck%20out%20Business%20Insider's%20source%20guide%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20for%20tips%20on%20sharing%20information%20securely.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhappiness-at-work-employee-engagement-fulfillment-flexibility-four-days-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702119121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65733bbc0ec98e92f74d8142%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhappiness-at-work-employee-engagement-fulfillment-flexibility-four-days-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Some%20employers%20are%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20keep%20their%20workers%20happy%20and%20combat%20burnout%20but%20unless%20bosses%20embrace%20flexibility%2C%20it'll%20be%20hard%20to%20succeed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dsiu%40insider.com%20(Diamond%20Naga%20Siu%2CTim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhappiness-at-work-employee-engagement-fulfillment-flexibility-four-days-