I've%20worked%20as%20a%20social%20media%20specialist%20at%20a%20discount%20grocery%20app%20called%20Flashfood%20in%20a%20remote%2C%209-to-5%20position%20since%202020.%20I%20used%20to%20have%20a%20more%20flexible%20job%2C%20but%20I%20quit%20because%20I%20wanted%20the%20security%20of%20a%209-to-5.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20graduated%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto%20in%202018%20and%20my%20first%20job%20was%20at%20a%20social%20media%20marketing%20agency%20in%20Toronto.%20I%20often%20felt%20more%20like%20a%20contractor%20than%20a%20secure%20employee%20because%20it%20was%20a%20startup%20with%20flexible%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20focused%20on%20helping%20bars%20and%20restaurants%20get%20their%20social%20media%20profiles%20up%20and%20running%2C%20but%20it%20didn't%20have%20the%20most%20consistent%20client%20roster.%20Since%20I%20was%20newer%20and%20had%20less%20experience%20on%20the%20job%2C%20I%20was%20sort%20of%20on%20the%20swing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20had%20more%20clients%2C%20I'd%20work%20more%20hours%2C%20but%20otherwise%20I%20didn't%20really%20have%20a%20consistent%20paycheck.%20Things%20slowed%20down%20even%20more%20doing%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20in%202020%20because%20a%20lot%20of%20restaurants%20and%20bars%20closed%20down%2C%20so%20my%20days%20weren't%20as%20full.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20just%20started%20to%20feel%20demoralized%20about%20all%20of%20the%20flexibility%20in%20my%20life%20and%20I%20wanted%20consistency%20so%20that%20I%20was%20waking%20up%20for%20something%20everyday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ended%20up%20leaving%20the%20agency%20to%20join%20Flashfood%20because%20I%20wanted%20the%20structure%20of%20a%209-to-5%20and%20the%20benefits%20it%20offered.%20For%20example%2C%20I%20really%20wanted%20to%20start%20therapy%20for%20the%20first%20time%20and%20I%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20do%20it%20unless%20I%20was%20getting%20health%20benefits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20a%209-to-5%20job%20felt%20like%20a%20a%20rite%20of%20passage%20and%20a%20coming%20of%20age%20moment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20feel%20like%20I%20have%20more%20time%20now%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20stable%20job%20brought%20certain%20changes%20to%20my%20life.%20I%20started%20taking%20better%20care%20of%20myself%20because%20there%20were%20more%20people%20that%20I%20had%20to%20answer%20to%20in%20the%20morning.%20There's%20some%20accountability%20in%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wake%20up%20earlier%20and%20make%20an%20effort%20to%20exercise%20and%20make%20myself%20a%20nice%20breakfast%2C%20before%20I%20have%20to%20sit%20down%20and%20hunker%20in%20for%20the%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20work%20I%20can%20make%20a%20lot%20more%20plans%20with%20my%20friends%20now.%20In%20the%20summers%2C%20at%205%20p.m.%2C%20I'm%20shutting%20my%20computer%20and%20walking%20down%20the%20street%20to%20a%20nice%20patio%20and%20meeting%20a%20couple%20of%20girl%20friends%20for%20a%20drink.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20have%20a%20weekly%20%26quot%3BSurvivor%26quot%3B%20night%20at%20my%20house.%20My%20friends%20come%20over%20and%20watch%20the%20%26quot%3BSurvivor%26quot%3B%20TV%20show%20on%20Wednesdays%20and%20I%20make%20them%20a%20big%20dinner.%20It's%20easier%20for%20me%20to%20schedule%20my%20personal%20life%20into%20my%20week%20rather%20than%20with%20a%20flexible%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20feel%20like%20I%20have%20more%20time%20now%20than%20when%20I%20was%20working%20more%20flexible%20hours%20because%20I%20have%20a%20better%20sense%20of%20what%20my%20plan%20for%20the%20week%20is.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20definitely%20don't%20feel%20like%20my%20job%20is%20soul-crushing%20and%20I%20don't%20feel%20like%20the%20hours%20are%20soul-crushing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20was%20still%20working%20a%20flexible%20hours%20job%2C%20I%20would%20be%20ordering%20takeout%20way%20more%20often%20and%20spending%20much%20more%20money.%20That%20didn't%20feel%20great.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20remotely%20makes