C%20the%20biography%20appears%20to%20be%20woefully%20incomplete%20and%20inadequate%20as%20a%20biography%20%3Cem%3Equa%3C%2Fem%3E%20biography.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20194px)%2085vw%2C%20194px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F07204529%2Fimage-1585-194x300.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22194%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F07204529%2Fimage-1585-194x300.png%20194w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F07204529%2Fimage-1585.png%20427w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688175%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Secret%20Life%20of%20John%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20By%20Adam%20Sisman%20(Profile%20Books)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELe%20Carr%C3%A9%20had%20insisted%20that%20all%20his%20countless%20love%20affairs%20be%20left%20out%20by%20Sisman%20in%20the%20biography.%20Sisman%20now%20reveals%20that%20while%20these%20tortuous%20negotiations%20regarding%20exclusion%20and%20censorship%20were%20going%20on%2C%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20eldest%20son%2C%20Simon%2C%20came%20to%20him%20and%20suggested%20that%20Sisman%20create%20%E2%80%9Ca%20secret%20annexe%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20material%20that%20was%20being%20left%20out%20and%20publish%20it%20after%20the%20death%20of%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Jane.%20This%20book%20grows%20out%20of%20that%20secret%20annexe.%20It%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20an%20indispensable%20complement%20to%20Sisman%E2%80%99s%20original%20biography.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20abundantly%20clear%20from%20this%20book%20that%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20(David%20Cornwell%20was%20his%20real%20name)%20was%20a%20compulsive%20womanizer%20(a%20word%20he%20loathed).%20He%20was%20also%20a%20congenital%20liar%20%E2%80%93%20to%20his%20wives%2C%20to%20his%20sons%2C%20to%20his%20lovers%2C%20to%20his%20friends%2C%20and%20to%20his%20biographer.%20He%20was%20a%20constant%20and%20a%20compulsive%20fabricator.%20Cornwell%20may%20have%20inherited%20or%20absorbed%20the%20infamous%20art%20of%20duplicity%20from%20his%20father%20Ronnie%2C%20a%20con%20man%20and%20an%20occasional%20jailbird.%20A%20famous%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20aphorism%20is%20%E2%80%9CSpying%20is%20lying%E2%80%9D.%20One%20could%20turn%20it%20around%20and%20say%20that%20for%20le%20Carr%C3%A9-Cornwell%2C%20living%20was%20lying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20level%2C%20this%20book%20is%20no%20more%20than%20an%20account%20of%20a%20great%20writer%E2%80%99s%20philandering.%20Women%2C%20as%20proper%20names%2C%20flit%20through%20the%20pages%20as%20objects%20and%20victims%20of%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20lust.%20They%20appear%20as%20cardboard%20characters.%20There%20seems%20to%20be%20no%20discernible%20pattern%20in%20the%20kind%20of%20women%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20preferred%20as%20his%20lovers%2Fmistresses.%20He%20seems%20to%20have%20taken%20to%20bed%20any%20woman%20that%20fell%20for%20his%20charm%20and%20flattered%20his%20gigantic%20male%20ego.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20two%20elements%20are%20common%20to%20his%20innumerable%20dalliances.%20One%2C%20he%20showered%20his%20lovers%20with%20expensive%20gifts%2C%20mostly%20jewellery%2C%20and%20took%20them%20for%20holidays%20often%20to%20exotic%20locations%20or%20luxurious%20hotels.%20The%20other%20is%20the%20elaborate%20steps%20he%20took%20to%20keep%20his%20affairs%20secret%20%E2%80%93%20false%20names%2C%20dead%20letter%20boxes%20and%20all%20the%20various%20procedures%2Frules%20he%20would%20make%20his%20spies%20use%20as%20tradecraft%20in%20his%20novels%2C%20John%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20broke%20the%20James%20Bond%20stereotype%20but%20David%20Cornwell%2C%20so%20far%20as%20women%20were%20concerned%2C%20behaved%20like%20James%20Bond%20with%20a%20self-given%20licence%20to%20break%20hearts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20another%20and%20a%20more%20serious%20level%2C%20Sisman%20is%20not%20engaged%20in%20an%20exercise%20in%20prurience%20or%20voyeurism.%20His%20attempt%20is%20to%20trace%20a%20link%20between%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20frequent%20acts%20of%20adultery%20and%20betrayal%20and%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20fiction.%20His%20argument%20is%20that%20le%20Carre%E2%80%99s%20libido%20provided%20the%20stimulus%20to%20his%20writing%20and%20that%20some%20of%20the%20women%20he%20was%20involved%20with%20became%2C%20at%20different%20points%20of%20time%2C%20his%20muse%2C%20albeit%20transient%20ones.%20The%20key%20to%20this%20argument%20is%20something%20that%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20wrote%20to%20Sisman%20when%20the%20two%20of%20them%20were%20discussing%20the%20former%E2%80%99s%20private%20life.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20infidelities%E2%80%9D%2C%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9Cproduced%20in%20my%20life%20a%20duality%20and%20a%20tension%20that%20became%20almost%20a%20necessary%20drug%20for%20my%20writing%2C%20a%20dangerous%20edge%20of%20some%20kind%E2%80%A6They%20are%20not%20therefore%20a%20%E2%80%98dark%20part%E2%80%99%20of%20my%20life%2C%20separate%20from%20the%20%E2%80%98highly%20literary%20calling%E2%80%99%2C%20so%20to%20speak%2C%20but%2C%20alas%2C%20integral%20to%20it%2C%20and%20inseparable.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20to%20put%20too%20fine%20a%20point%20on%20it%2C%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20was%20telling%20Sisman%20that%20he%20needed%20the%20sex%20and%20the%20secrecy%20to%20enable%20him%20to%20write.%20An%20unsympathetic%20reader%20would%20say%20that%20this%20is%20a%20most%20convenient%20alibi%20for%20an%20unstoppable%20philanderer%20and%20user%20of%20women.%20Note%20the%20use%20of%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Calas%E2%80%9D%20to%20suggest%20that%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20regretted%20this%20predicament.%20Was%20he%20being%20sincere%3F%20The%20question%20is%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20evident%20from%20whatever%20Sisman%20has%20written%20%E2%80%93%20in%20this%20book%20and%20in%20the%20biography%20%E2%80%93%20that%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20was%20not%20averse%20to%20knowingly%20and%20deliberately%20speaking%20the%20untruth.%20He%20fabricated%20his%20past%2C%20and%20according%20to%20his%20convenience%2C%20he%20gave%20different%20versions%20of%20the%20same%20anecdote%3B%20he%20committed%20himself%20to%20undying%20love%20to%20the%20woman%20who%20at%20that%20time%20was%20sharing%20his%20bed%20only%20to%20break%20that%20commitment%20the%20next%20day%20or%20in%20the%20near%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20fiction%20writer%2C%20fiction%20came%20naturally%20to%20him.%20Thus%2C%20the%20question%20inevitably%20arises%20over%20how%20far%20we%20can%20take%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20at%20his%20word%20in%20the%20passage%20quoted%20above%20%E2%80%93%20both%20in%20its%20expression%20of%20regret%20and%20the%20statement%20that%20sex%20and%20secrecy%20were%20the%20drugs%20he%20needed%20to%20write.%20There%20is%20no%20apparent%20reason%20to%20take%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20at%20his%20word.%20But%20in%20this%20instance%2C%20Sisman%2C%20for%20reasons%20not%20explained%2C%20does.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresumably%2C%20Sisman%E2%80%99s%20justification%20is%20that%20he%20needed%20to%20find%20a%20plausible%20reason%20for%20his%20subject%E2%80%99s%20infidelities.%20On%20the%20face%20of%20it%2C%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20self-serving%20justification%20%E2%80%93%20that%20writing%20about%20a%20secret%20world%20draws%20inspiration%20from%20the%20writer%E2%80%99s%20secret%20life%20%E2%80%93%20has%20a%20faint%20ring%20of%20plausibility.%20But%20Sisman%E2%80%99s%20book%20would%20have%20been%20better%20served%20if%20he%20had%20chosen%20against%20swallowing%20the%20%3Cem%3Enon%20sequitur%3C%2Fem%3E%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20offers.%20Promiscuity%20and%20adultery%2C%20even%20among%20great%20writers%20and%20artists%2C%20neither%20requires%20nor%20always%20has%20a%20perfectly%20or%20even%20seemingly%20reasonable%20explanation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20an%20even%20more%20serious%20problem%20is%20that%20Sisman%20is%20unable%20to%20convincingly%20show%20how%20and%20when%20and%20which%20of%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20women%20did%20genuinely%20serve%20as%20his%20muse.%20Sue%20Dawson%20comes%20nearest%20but%20that%20perception%20on%20her%20part%20was%20shattered%20and%20was%20shown%20to%20be%20a%20complete%20delusion.%20At%20best%2C%20what%20Sisman%20does%20is%20to%20suggest%20that%20such%20and%20such%20lover%20served%20as%20the%20model%20of%20a%20character%20in%20one%20of%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20novels.%20A%20model%20is%20not%20a%20muse.%20Le%20Carr%C3%A9%20once%20wrote%20(again%20no%20need%20to%20believe%20him)%20that%20he%20once%20saw%20in%20an%20airport%20bar%20a%20weary%20man%20in%20a%20crumpled%20mac%20and%20this%20figure%20served%20as%20the%20model%20for%20Alec%20Leamas%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Spy%20Who%20Came%20in%20from%20the%20Cold%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Hardly%20a%20muse!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20any%20worthwhile%20pursuit%20of%20the%20theme%20of%20adultery%20in%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20fiction%20and%20Cornwell%E2%80%99s%20life%2C%20one%20has%20to%20address%20the%20character%20of%20Ann%20Smiley%2C%20who%20makes%20cameo%20appearances%20in%20all%20the%20Smiley%20novels%2C%20beginning%20with%20the%20very%20first%2C%20%3Cem%3ECall%20for%20the%20Dead%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20but%20is%20an%20inescapable%20and%20constant%20presence%20in%20George%20Smiley%E2%80%99s%20life.%20Ann%20and%20George%20are%20apart%20and%20not%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELe%20Carr%C3%A9%20made%20Ann%20a%20serial%20adulterer%20taking%20all%20and%20sundry%20to%20her%20bed%20%E2%80%93%20from%20Bill%20Haydon%2C%20the%20Circus%20mole%2C%20a%20racing%20car%20driver%2C%20a%20ballet%20dancer%20and%20so%20on.%20Why%20did%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20fashion%20Ann%E2%80%99s%20character%20in%20this%20manner%3F%20Was%20Ann%20Smiley%20a%20female%20image%20of%20le%20Carr%C3%A9-Cornwell%3F%20Such%20questions%20are%20not%20raised%20by%20Sisman.%20Pity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarla%20in%20%3Cem%3ETinker%20Tailor%20Soldier%20Spy%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20told%20Haydon%20that%20Smiley%20%E2%80%9Chad%20this%20one%20price%3A%20Ann.%20The%20last%20illusion%20of%20an%20illusionless%20man.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20was%20talking%20about%20himself.%20He%20had%20this%20one%20price%3A%20love%2C%20and%20he%20pursued%20the%20illusion%20of%20love%20as%20John%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%20and%20David%20Cornwell.%20The%20latter%20at%20his%20worst%20(Sisman%E2%80%99s%20words)%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20a%20liar%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20former%20%E2%80%9Cat%20his%20best%20was%20a%20truth-teller%E2%80%99%E2%80%99.%20The%20distinction%20between%20the%20real%20and%20assumed%20names%20is%20important%20for%20the%20biographer%2C%20the%20literary%20critic%2C%20and%20the%20reader.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERudrangshu%20Mukherjee%20is%20chancellor%20and%20professor%20of%20history%20at%20Ashoka%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702042239000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08125143%2Fimage-1586.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-intricacies-of-john-le-carres-secret-life-through-the-lens-of-adam-sismans-revelations%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20lifetime%2C%20Adam%20Sisman%20had%20published%20a%20massive%20biography%20of%20the%20writer.%20It%20now%20transpires%20from%20Sisman%E2%80%99s%20new%20book%20that%20at%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20insistence%2C%20Sisman%20was%20forced%20to%20exclude%20large%20chunks%20of%20le%20Carr%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20private%20life%20from%20the%20biography.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-intricacies-of-john-le-carres-secret-life-through-the-lens-of-adam-sismans-revelations%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Photos%20show%20Notre-Dame%20restoration%20work%20after%20devastating%202019%20fire%20-%20a%20year%20before%20planned%20reopening%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%