ut%20with%20recent%20events%20may%20be%20reaching%20its%20nadir.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20we%20look%20at%20the%20present%20Middle%20East%2C%20we%20see%20a%20situation%20where%20post%20the%20Iraq%20war%20and%20the%20removal%20of%20Saddam%20Hussein%2C%20the%20influence%20of%20Iran%20has%20extended%20to%20Iraq%2C%20a%20Shia%20majority%20country%2C%20upsetting%20the%20equipoise%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20between%20the%20Shia%20and%20Sunni%20Arab.%20The%20removal%20of%20Saddam%20led%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20Sunni%20extremism%20in%20the%20form%20of%20ISIS%20which%20spread%20to%20Syria%20and%20led%20to%20a%20rag-tag%20coalition%20assisted%20by%20the%20West%20and%20the%20Gulf%20Arabs%20challenging%20the%20Alawite%20hegemony%20of%20the%20Assads%20in%20Syria.%20Lebanon%20remains%20on%20edge%2C%20with%20the%20Shia%20and%20the%20Palestinians%20looking%20to%20Hezbollah%20for%20protection%20against%20the%20incursions%20of%20Israel.%20Libya%20is%20an%20egregious%20example%20of%20Western%20intervention%20%E2%80%93%20led%20by%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20and%20David%20Cameron%2C%20backed%20by%20a%20reluctant%20Barack%20Obama%20%E2%80%93%20in%20deposing%20General%20Muammar%20Gaddafi%20causing%20the%20dismantling%20of%20the%20Libyan%20State%2C%20the%20promotion%20of%20warlords%2C%20militias%2C%20encouraging%20fundamentalism%20in%20neighbouring%20countries%20and%20being%20one%20of%20the%20prime%20causes%20of%20mass%20migration%20and%20human%20trafficking%20from%20Africa%20to%20Europe.%20These%20are%20only%20a%20few%20examples%2C%20but%20they%20are%20not%20edifying%20ones.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20366px)%2085vw%2C%20366px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08140538%2F71hUWGlgqFL._SL1500_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22366%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08140538%2F71hUWGlgqFL._SL1500_.jpg%20781w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08140538%2F71hUWGlgqFL._SL1500_-195x300.jpg%20195w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08140538%2F71hUWGlgqFL._SL1500_-666x1024.jpg%20666w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688294%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22562%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENigel%20Ashton%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EFalse%20Prophets%3A%20British%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Fateful%20Fascination%20with%20the%20Middle%20East%20from%20Suez%20to%20Syria%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EAtlantic%20Books%20(March%202022)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20book%20relates%20how%20even%20a%20middle-level%20ex-colonial%20power%20such%20as%20the%20UK%20has%20exercised%20an%20outsize%20and%20largely%20malign%20influence%20on%20the%20developments%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20a%20role%20magnified%20when%20it%20joined%20with%20the%20US%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cspecial%20relationship%E2%80%9D%20described%20by%20Tony%20Blair%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Carticle%20of%20faith%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20it%20did%20in%20the%20Iraq%20war.%20Harold%20Macmillan%20once%20described%20the%20role%20of%20the%20British%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Equa%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20Americans%20as%20similar%20to%20the%20role%20played%20by%20the%20Greeks%20to%20the%20Romans%2C%20and%20indeed%20the%20British%20have%20provided%20intellectual%20heft%20for%20much%20of%20the%20dysfunctional%20interference%20and%20bungling%20that%20has%20occurred%20in%20the%20post-war%20period.%20It%20also%20extirpates%20the%20fallacy%20that%20the%20Suez%20crisis%20marked%20the%20end%20of%20British%20imperialism%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20it%20did%20no%20such%20thing.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20fascination%20that%20the%20Middle%20East%20exercises%20over%20British%20politicians%20causing%20the%20British%20government%20to%20interfere%20in%20various%20wars%2C%20depositions%20of%20monarchs%2C%20and%20providing%20unwavering%20support%20for%20the%20Israeli%20position%20over%20the%20years%20has%20been%20truly%20remarkable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fevent%2FSuez-Crisis%5C%22%3ESuez%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20led%20to%20the%20downfall%20of%20Sir%20Anthony%20Eden%2C%20a%20politician%2C%20who%20rightly%20opposed%20appeasement%20but%20mistook%20a%20nationalist%20leader%2C%20Gamal%20Abdel%20Nasser%2C%20for%20a%20new%20Hitler%20and%20together%20with%20the%20French%20and%20Israelis%20took%20over%20the%20Suez%20Canal%2C%20as%20Eden%20had%20the%20presentiment%20that%20Nasser%20would%20use%20this%20vital%20trade%20route%20to%20strangle%20Britain.%20The%20conservative%20perceptions%20and%20policies%20%E2%80%93%20under%20prime%20ministers%20Macmillan%20and%20Alec%20Douglas-Home%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecan%20be%20seen%20through%20the%20prism%20of%20colonialism%20and%20antagonism%20towards%20nationalist%20leaders%20such%20as%20Nasser%20and%20Mossadegh%20of%20Iran.%20Whilst%2C%20that%20was%20bad%20enough%2C%20the%20Left%20has%20been%20much%20worse.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Labour%20Party%20were%20infatuated%20with%20the%20faux%20socialism%20of%20the%20Kibbutzim%2C%20conveniently%20ignoring%20the%20fact%20that%20many%20of%20them%20were%20constructed%20on%20land%20which%20belonged%20to%20the%20Palestinian%20Arabs%20who%20in%201948%20were%20forced%20out%20of%20their%20territory%20by%20the%20Israelis%20and%20gangs%20who%20would%20today%20qualify%20as%20terrorists.%20The%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20Palestinians%20were%20evacuated%20from%20their%20historic%20lands%20was%20justified%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20appalling%20legacy%20of%20the%20holocaust.%20Many%20Labour%20politicians%20were%20friends%20with%20the%20early%20Zionists%20such%20as%20Ben%20Gurion%2C%20and%20Golda%20Meier.%20But%20beyond%20socialism%2C%20there%20was%20religion%2C%20at%20least%20three%20of%20the%20Labour%20Prime%20Ministers%20who%20were%20the%20most%20fervent%20of%20Zionists%2C%20such%20as%20Wilson%2C%20Callaghan%20and%20Blair%20were%20animated%20by%20biblical%20fervour%2C%20ignoring%20the%20fact%20that%20some%20of%20the%20most%20prominent%20Palestinian%20leaders%20were%20secular%20and%20many%20of%20them%20Christians.%20In%20Tony%20Blair%2C%20we%20see%20the%20distillation%20of%20an%20almost%20Manichean%20ideology%20post%209%2F11%2C%20where%20the%20world%20is%20broken%20down%20into%20good%20and%20evil%2C%20that%20these%20attacks%20on%20that%20fateful%20day%20presaged%20a%20civilisational%20challenge%20to%20the%20West%20and%20freedom.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhilst%20there%20is%20this%20neo-conservative%20argument%20that%20the%20Middle%20East%20needs%20democracy%20and%20freedom%2C%20an%20intellectual%20justification%20for%20toppling%20what%20are%20seen%20as%20authoritarian%20rulers%2C%20this%20argument%20camouflages%20a%20point%20that%20many%20thinking%20Arabs%20see.%20First%2C%20this%20is%20convenient%20to%20the%20West%20when%20the%20rulers%20are%20anti-Western%20or%20nationalist.%20But%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20Kingdom%20of%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20a%20fundamentalist%20authoritarian%20dictatorship%20which%20has%20traditionally%20been%20a%20Western%20ally%2C%20these%20rules%20do%20not%20apply%20%E2%80%93%20although%20under%20crown%20prince%20Mohammed%20bin%20Salman%20this%20is%20changing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESecondly%2C%20and%20this%20emerges%20strongly%20in%20Ashton%E2%80%99s%20book%2C%20is%20the%20religious%20element%2C%20particularly%20in%20relation%20to%20Zionism%2C%20which%20influences%20Western%20policy.%20The%20Jewish%20lobby%20has%20historically%20supported%20Zionism%2C%20Lord%20Rothschild%20was%20influential%20in%20promoting%20what%20became%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Ffeatures%2F2018%2F11%2F2%2Fmore-than-a-century-on-the-balfour-declaration-explained%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Balfour%2520Declaration%252C%2520which%2520resulted%2Cfor%2520the%2520Jewish%2520people%25E2%2580%259D%2520there.%5C%22%3EBalfour%20Declaration%20in%201917%3C%2Fa%3E%20setting%20out%20the%20basis%20for%20a%20Jewish%20homeland%20in%20Palestine.%20US%20policy%20has%20been%20influenced%20by%20this%20lobby%20ever%20since%20Israel%20was%20formed.%20But%2C%20even%20more%20seminal%20has%20been%20the%20role%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fhow-the-strident-support-of-evangelical-christians-to-israel-undermines-the-palestine-cause%5C%22%3Eevangelical%20Christians%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%2C%20apparently%20from%20Ashton%E2%80%99s%20book%2C%20Labour%20politicians%20such%20as%20Wilson%2C%20Callaghan%2C%20Blair%20and%20Brown%2C%20who%20have%20indulged%20Israel%20and%20the%20latter%20two%20did%20nothing%20to%20prevent%20the%20colonisation%20of%20the%20West%20Bank%20by%20Israeli%20settlers%20rendering%20the%20two-state%20solution%20academic%2C%20leaving%20over%205%20million%20Palestinians%20without%20citizenship%20or%20nationality%2C%20making%20them%20the%20nowhere%20people.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20course%2C%20Britain%20as%20a%20middle%20level%20power%20does%20have%20its%20limitations%2C%20but%20at%20least%20if%20we%20hark%20back%20to%20Macmillan%2C%20the%20British%20role%20as%20mentor%20to%20the%20US%20gave%20legitimacy%20to%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20approach%20on%20important%20issues.%20George%20W.%20Bush%20relied%20heavily%20on%20Blair%E2%80%99s%20support%20and%20guidance%20in%20going%20to%20war%20with%20Iraq%2C%20but%20once%20the%20war%20started%2C%20Blair%20was%20marginalised%20and%20so%20was%20the%20experience%20of%20the%20British%2C%20which%20could%20have%20made%20a%20difference%20to%20the%20end%20game.%20The%20Iraq%20imbroglio%20proved%20a%20major%20own%20goal%20for%20the%20West%2C%20handing%20over%20a%20significant%20Arab%20country%20and%20oil%20producer%20to%20the%20Iranian%20camp%20as%20well%20as%20causing%20Sunni%20disaffection%20in%20the%20form%20of%20ISIS.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20people%20fail%20to%20understand%20is%20that%20the%20Middle%20East%20does%20exercise%20a%20disproportionate%20influence%20on%20world%20affairs.%20Post%20the%20Yom%20Kippur%20war%2C%20the%20European%20experiment%20with%20social%20democracy%20foundered%2C%20with%20oil%20prices%20rising%20dramatically%20by%20virtue%20of%20the%20OPEC%20boycott.%20The%20introduction%20of%20the%20petro%20dollar%20led%20to%20the%20expansion%20of%20American%20power%20and%20influence%20as%20the%20present%20situation%20with%20America%20funding%20two%20wars%2C%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20Gaza%2C%20may%20now%20signal%20the%20irreversible%20decline%20of%20such%20power.%20The%20price%20of%20the%20petro%20dollar%20was%20the%20US%20giving%20carte%20blanch%20to%20the%20Wahhabis%20in%20Saudi%20Arabia%20to%20spread%20their%20pernicious%20version%20of%20Islam%20throughout%20the%20Muslim%20world%20and%20funding%20Jihad.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPerhaps%20if%20the%20West%20had%20adopted%20a%20more%20rational%20and%20equitable%20approach%20to%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20these%20countries%20and%20the%20world%20would%20be%20spared%20such%20suffering%20and%20distress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpreview%2F688262%5C%22%3EJaved%20Gaya%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20Bombay%20high%20court%20lawyer%20who%20is%20currently%20writing%20a%20book%20on%20the%20historical%2C%20geographical%20and%20political%20impact%20of%20partition%20on%20India%20and%20the%20wider%20sub-continent%2C%20particularly%20with%20reference%20to%20the%20Indian%20Muslims%20and%20other%20minorities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702035022000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08140538%2F71hUWGlgqFL._SL1500_.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Ffalse-prophets-evidence-of-the-wests-neo-colonial-c